The '''United States Senate election of 1878''' was an election which had the [[Democratic Party (United States)| Democratic Party]] retake control of the [[United States Senate]] for the first time since before the [[American Civil War|Civil War]].

As this election was prior to ratification of the [[Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|seventeenth amendment]], Senators were chosen by [[State legislature (United States)|State legislatures]].

== Results ==
[[46th United States Congress|46th Congress]] (1879â1881) 

* Majority Party: Democratic (42)
* Minority Party: Republican (33)
* Other Parties: Independent (1)
* '''Total Seats: 76'''

